review_blob: Not bad. Aroma is coffee and roasted notes. Flavor is similar, its just like any nitro dry stout. Coffee is present. Creamy as hell. Nice
Pint had at the source. Aroma is huge tropical aromas and citrus. Flavor is full on tangerine/tangelo. Very good. Im a huge fan of brews made with motueka hops and this brew didnt disappoint.

Bottle at home. Aroma was fudge, raisins, vinous notes, cocoa. Creamy mouthfeel and that jet black CCB stout quality Ive come to expect. Low carb, no head. Flavor was booze and raisins. I got a hint of sour mixed in the fudge/fruity flavors. Im not sure if that was intended but it wasnt off putting.
beer_name: Cigar City Endless Nameless Bourbon Barrel-Aged Imperial Stout

review_blob: On tap at the brewery. Aroma is light banana/clove, some citrus. Flavor is more of that. The citrus flavor is light. Belgian yeast note is ok.
beer_name: St. Pete Three Toed Paw Belgian Pale Ale

review_blob: On draft at the source. Aroma is lightly grassy hops, bready caramel notes. Flavor is the same. The hops were drowned out a bit by the malt, but its not a horrible brew.

Bottle into snifter. Aroma is dark fruits, chocolate, roast, plum, light soy sauce, earth. Pour is jet black, tan head. Flavor is light berries, brownies, cocoa, coffee, earth. Its quite a rich brew, quite nice.
Pint, on site. Aroma is caramel malts, some rye, grass. Flavor is mainly caramel malts with not a lot more going on the. The rye was lost to me in the flavor. Nice, either way.

Bottle at home. Aroma is grass and citrus, some hay. Flavor is mainly citrus hops, slightly bitter notes, grass, some light biscuity malts. Overall, this is quite a well balanced brew and an enjoyable pilsener.

Scotch ale? this had a ton of smoked notes all around with some caramel and bready notes in the mix. It wasnt horrible but it wasnt what I was looking for in a scotch ale. That being said, i like smoked beers but this seemed to be in the middle of two styles.

Bottle at home. Aroma is roasted notes, chocolate, coffee, caramel notes, lactose sweetness. Flavor is much the same. Im digging this being a big, full flavored stout that doesnt linger into the soy sauce side of stouts that I see a lot of lately. Great stuff.
beer_name: Funky Buddha Nikolai Vorlauf Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Bottle at home, into snifter. Aroma is pure milk chocolate, lactose, nestle chocolate chips. Flavor is sweet chocolate, a touch of roast, sweetness from the lactose. Very nice.
beer_name: Funky Buddha Nib Smuggler Chocolate Milk Porter

review_blob: Bottle. Aroma is big time citrus and grapefruit. Flavor is similar. Tangerine and full-on grapefruit are all shes got. I found it quite enjoyable, as I am a big fan of grapefruit.

Bottle, shared with many at my birthday party as a celebration of my first born son. Aroma is chocolate, roast, fudge, vinous notes, soy, molasses. Pours black. Basically no head on this one. Flavor is more soy and molasses on the aftertaste. The sherry notes were almost lost on me. It had a hint of oxidation to it. Not bad at all but it seemed to be my least favorite version of this beer that Ive had.
beer_name: Cigar City Marshal Zhukovs Imperial Stout (Sherry Barrel)

review_blob: Bottle at home. Its bready, caramel-y, malty. Its an average, drinkable marzen.
Awesome beer. Bottle, WH ABC. Aroma is tropical fruits, mangoes, passion fruit, big hops, lemon, tangerine. Flavor follows suit. Big tropical notes, a hint of sweetness and huge hop flavor. Awesome!
beer_name: Boulevard Collaboration No. 5 Tropical Pale Ale

review_blob: Bottle at home. Aroma is light roasted notes, earthy pumpkin, lightly spiced. I think the best thing about this beer is that you can actually taste the pumpkin in it. Not the spices or added "pumpkin" flavors, but real, roasted pumpkin that has a roasted, earthy flavor. Not too sweet and spiced just right. Good stuff.

Thanks to ABC Winter Haven for ordering this for me. Aroma is orange zest and tart, sour funk. Pours a pinkish hue. Flavor is all sour with a hint of citrus. The salt is rather hidden to me. The puckering sour overpowers everything but its refreshing and not a bad beer by any means.
beer_name: Anderson Valley Highway 128 Blood Orange Gose

review_blob: Bottle at home, purchased from ABC Winter Haven. Aroma is Belgian yeast, peppery, hay or straw notes. Pours a golden blonde with a fluffy white head that dies out. Flavor is crisp citrus notes, some peppery flavors, spices. Overall, its quite dry. Not bad.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Ovila Saison - Mandarin Orange & Peppercorns

review_blob: Bottle at home, thanks to Andrew for gifting me a sixer. Aroma is pine and citrus, caramel, hay. Flavor matches up. Its a decent brew.

Bottle at home. Aroma is dark chocolate, roast, cinnamon, cocoa, earthy notes. Pours dark black, khaki head. Flavot is heavy on the cinnamon. Roasted earthy notes and a touch of booze round it out. Nice but the cinnamon gave me heart burn immediately.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Imperial Stout X - Aztec Chocolate

review_blob: Bottle at home. Aroma is roasted grain, light coffee, chocolate, toast. Pour is clear brown, nice head. Flavot is roasted malts, toasted bread, chocolate, sweet grain, minerals. Very nice.

Big thanks to Harold for sending me two of these. Aroma and flavor are straight up orange juice and hop goodness. It simple but bold in its flavors. I could have had a bunch of these back to back and still wanted another. Very nice.
beer_name: DuClaw Hop Continuum No. 1 (Blood Orange Gypsy)

review_blob: Bottle thanks to Chipalsa. Huge coffee aromas and roast hit the nose. Chocolate notes. Espresso. Flavor is bold coffee, chocolate, iced coffee. This thing is on point for a coffee stout.
Bottle thanks to Harold. Nose is huge citrus. Grapefruit, tangerine, some tropical notes. Flavor matches up nicely. Very intensely fruited. I loved it!

A big thanks to my buddy Harold (aka chipalsa). This is my kind of brew. Aroma is peanut butter, roast, cocoa, coffee. Pours a black body, tan head. Flavor is spot on roasted malts with not overbearing peanut butter flavor. It was like a Reeses cup in a glass, less sweet. Awesome stuff.

Ahhh...a nice smoked beer. A style I fancy. Aroma is medium smoke and roast, sweet notes of the malt. Pour is super clear golden brown. Flavor is sweet caramel, toffee, medium smoke. Very nice and well balanced.

Bottle into snifter. Aroma is butterscotch, bourbon, some light vanilla, pumpkin spices. Pours a dark brown, tan head. Flavor is butterscotch, sweet lingering notes of bourbon and pumpkin. Overall its pretty good and for $1.00 a bomber, it cant be beat!!

Six pack of bottles. Aroma is bread, honey, biscuit, grass, faint citrus. This thing is crystal effing clear. Fluffy white head. Flavor is on the dry side. I see others say its sweeter but not from what Ive had, or, my palate must be used to even sweeter brews/tastes. Overall its not bad. I didnt care too much for the first bottle I had but it grew on my throughout the last two weeks of sipping on a bottle here and there.

Hmmm...an interesting brew. Aroma is corn and Pilsner malt. Grass. The aroma is very faint. Flavor is light and underwhelming which is what the label says it is to be so no hard feelings. Lightly sweet and refreshing malt. Not bad for a hot day.
beer_name: Bold City Killer Whale Cream Ale

review_blob: Bottle served in a ceramic mug. Aroma is honey, light spice, wheat, Belgian-esque notes. Flavor is light and playful. Wheat and spice and grassy notes. Very timid brew but pleasing.

Bottle. Aroma is grain, sweet malt, lemon. Flavor is big sweet grain flavor, a light grassy hop. The malt profile is excellent. I really enjoyed drinking this brew. I would pick it up regularly if I could.
beer_name: Toppling Goliath Dorothys New World Lager

review_blob: Bottle from sister-in-laws boyfriend. Nose is juicy citrus and tropical fruit. Huge hop aroma. Flavor is full on citrus with a light malt bite to even it out. Pale ale? Maybe thats what they call it. More like an IPA, but who knows or cares now a days. Its a damn fine brew.
Can at home. Aroma is citrus hops, caramel malt, buttery notes. Flavor is similar with a distinct buttery flavor in some cans versus others. Citrus hops and sweet Malta. Not bad.
A nice brew. Smoky aroma with roast and chocolate notes. Pours dark black, fluffy copper head. Flavor is ashy, smokey, chocolate notes. Medium bodies. Very nice.

Bottle at home. Aroma is rich coffee, dark chocolate, roast, vanilla, barrel. Pours super black. Oily and thick. Flavor is nice, very similar to the aroma with a touch of soy. Sweet but not overly. I like how balanced this is for having so much flavor. The coffee flavors are very present amongst the barrel aging. Great!
beer_name: Cigar City Caff Americano Double Stout (Rum Barrel-Aged)

review_blob: Can served at home. Aroma is sweet key lime and grain. Flavor is straight up lime and pie crust. An easy drinker.

Wow. This was a crazy brew. Pours jet black with dark tan head. Thick looking in the glass. Aroma is roasted notes, chocolate, distinctly hoppy, a touch of vanilla. Flavor is light soy, vanilla, cocoa, citrus hops. A lot going on here but nice. Very thick palate and soft carbonation.
beer_name: Cigar City Da Un Beso A La Botella

review_blob: Bottle at home served in a teku glass. Aroma is citrus and pine with a dank note. Flavor is similar. Not bad.

Bottle served in a snifter at home. Cheers, Sue! You are missed. Aroma is watermelon and prickly pear fruit. Biting sour notes. Pour is a beautiful pinkish red color. Fizzy white head that fades quickly. Flavor is all fruit with a sharp lactic sour. Very refreshing, loaded with flavor. Great!!
beer_name: Cigar City / Cycle / 7venth Sun / J Wakefield A Beer Named Sue

review_blob: On tap at CCB. Honestly it resembles the flavor and aroma of maduro brown ale a lot. Roasted malts, caramel, bready notes, a hint of coffee. Earthiness and medium sweetness. Quite nice and full flavored for such a low abv. I would easily buy a sixer of this if they canned it.
beer_name: Cigar City This Wont Be Popular In The Tasting Room

review_blob: Bottle at home served into Unibroue tulip. Pours a nice pink hued body with hardly any head. Aroma and flavor is pure raspberry. Tart, lightly sweet, red raspberry flavor. The yeast notes are there but almost lost. Its a nice brew but not something I could drink on a regular basis. Maybe Im just burnt out on raspberries since I have huge bushes of them in my yard.
Bottle to mug. Aroma is light citrus, caramel, some spice. pours a nice brown color, fluffy head. citrus hops and caramel malt balance out nicely. Good stuff.
Bottle served in a chilled mug. Aroma was hay, grass, light citrus, bread. Flavor is crisp and refreshing with a bready malt and light grassy hops. Its how I would expect a pilsener to taste.

Bottle served poolside. Aroma is piney hops with some citrus. Flavor is semi bland actually. The hops seemed faint in flavor and the malts were just average with some light caramel and bread. Not bad but not something I would buy a sixer of.

Bottle at home. Coffee and roasted malts are the main aroma with a grapefruit hop bite. Flavor is well balanced with a good amount of roast but the hops shine through a bit more. This style has never been my favorite but I think this is a well done brew.
Bottle at home in snifter. Aroma is sweet chocolate, light roast, some earthy notes. Flavor is quite chocolatey. Big time sweet chocolate notes but not overpowering. Not bad.
Bottle at home. Aroma is wheat, cracker, light grass, banana/bubble gum. Flavor is similar with a more pronounced wheat flavor. Sessionable and overall quite nice.

Bottle at home while enjoying some movies. This one pours a dark, deep brown almost black color. Huge khaki head. Aroma is lightly roasted malts, fruity notes, saison yeast stands out. Flavor is similar with a lightly fruity, sweet note. Lightly peppery, some earthy chocolate that is gentle. Very different but quite nice!
beer_name: Ommegang Game of Thrones #5 - Three-Eyed Raven

review_blob: 4-pack, sipped on throughout the week. Aroma is piney, citrusy hops, caramel malts. Flavor is hop forward with a lot of pine tree flavor and thick caramel, sweet malts. Intensely flavored. Quite bitter.
Bottle. Aroma was skunky with some grass. Flavor is skunk, light malts, grass, corn.
